  "commentary": "With SPX at 6919.67 sitting between the GEX flip (6858) and max positive gamma wall (6950), dealers are currently long gamma and will mechanically sell into any rally toward 6950 while buying dips toward 6900. The massive positive gamma cluster from 6900-7000 creates a strong gravitational pull that should contain price action within this ~100-point range, with dealers providing liquidity against directional moves. Key levels to watch are the 6950 max gamma wall above (heavy dealer selling pressure) and 6900 support below (dealer buying interest), while a break below 6858 would flip the regime bearish.\n\nBottom line: expect sideways chop between 6900-6950 with dealers capping big moves in either direction.",
